        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued July 18 at 3:46PM MDT by NWS Pueblo CO</headline>
        <description>At 346 PM MDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm over
Divide, or 20 miles northwest of Colorado Springs, moving east at 15
mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 40 mph and half inch hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Woodland Park, Green Mountain Falls, Divide, Crystola, and
Florissant.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
